channel.title: Port forwarding Help!
channel.description: I've port forwarded 43594 on tcp, put my firewall to access 43594 in tcp & I went a canyouseeme.org. It told me it cannot see my 43594. I double checked everything in my router & the firewall to see if it was good and it was, still no luck. I got uTorrent and port forwarded there, and got some luck. In the website it said, it can access 43594 in my ip, but I can not log onto my server within localhost or any ip. I downloaded various other programs and canyouseeme.org said 43594 is accessible, but I simply CAN'T log onto localhost while it's running. I exited the programs and then I could log onto localhost, 0.0.0.0 & 127.0.0.1. What can be the problem? I've port forwarded many times, and even reset my router. I've had others do it over team viewer and still no luck. What can I do? :mad:
